com.mumfrey.liteloader.modconfig

Annotation Type ExposableOptions


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface ExposableOptions
    Annotation which can be a applied to mod classes to indicate that members decorated with the Gson Expose annotation should be serialised with Gson.
    Author:
    Adam Mummery-Smith

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean aggressive
      Set to true to disable write anti-hammer for config file
      java.lang.String filename
      Config file name, if not specified the mod class name is used
      ConfigStrategy strategy
      Configuration strategy to use
